<%= upcoming_presentations %>

<section class='thin column'>
  <article>
    <header><h2>join</h2></header>
    <ol class='join'>
      <li>Follow <a href='http://twitter.com/BostonRB' target='_blank'>@BostonRB</a> on Twitter</li>
      <li>Join the <a href='https://groups.google.com/group/boston-rubygroup' target='_blank'>BostonRB Mailing List</a></li>
      <li>Attend meetings and project nights</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
  <article>
    <header><h2>when</h2></header>
    <p>Second Tuesday of the month<br>7PM to 9PM</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <header><h2>where</h2></header>
    <p>
      <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=290+Congress+St+Boston+MA">Brightcove Offices</a><br/>
        290 Congress St<br/>
        Boston, MA<br/>
      <%= link_to 'Sign up required','http://guestlistapp.com/events/107814', :id => 'signup' %>
    </p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <header>
      <h2>what</h2>
    </header>
    <p>Boston Ruby is a local community of Rubyists and enthusiasts of open source software. The main event is the second Tuesday of every month. Those events entail one or two 45-minute presentations, lightning talks, and announcements.</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <header><h2>who</h2></header>
    <p>Experienced Rubyists are usually present and new Rubyists are always welcome!</p>
  </article>

  <article>
    <header><h2>more</h2></header>
    <p>
      <a href="http://project-night.bostonrb.org/">Project nights</a> happen on the first Tuesday of the month. We welcome all skill levels and encourage people that are "Ruby curious" to attend. At the Project Night people do things like getting their first Rails app running or writing and releasing <a href="http://rubygems.org">Ruby gems</a>.
      <br/><br/>
      We will be writing code so bring a laptop and enthusiasm. For those without a project idea be willing to help others.
    </p>
  </article>

</section>
